                             == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                                                                                                                      
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             A Jazzer fuzzing run against an Apache Tika RTF parser triggered a high-severity security finding (FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh) indicating potential Remote Code                        
                             Execution. The issue arises when the parser processes embedded objects in RTF data and uses Java deserialization (ObjectInputStream.readObject), allowing                           
                             unrestricted class or object creation based on untrusted input.                                                                                                                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Issue:                                                                                                                                                                            
                               The fuzzer exercised the Apache Tika RTF parsers embedded-object handler, which invokes Java deserialization on data extracted from an RTF document. During this                 
                             process, externally controlled input flows directly into an ObjectInputStream, enabling arbitrary class instantiation and potential remote code execution.                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Vulnerability Type:                                                                                                                                                               
                               Remote Code Execution via unsafe deserialization. The Jazzer framework categorizes this as a FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution, warning that                       
                             unrestricted object creation from untrusted data may lead to execution of attacker-supplied classes or code on the classpath.                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Key Observations:                                                                                                                                                                 
                               1. The stack trace shows `jaz.Zer.readObject` delegating to `java.io.ObjectInputStream.readObject`, indicating standard Java serialization is in use.                             
                               2. The vulnerable path is exercised in `org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject`, which is called by                                          
                             `TextExtractor.processGroupEnd` and ultimately by `RTFParser.parse`.                                                                                                                
                               3. The fuzzer harness (`com.example.RTFParserFuzzer.parseOne` and `fuzzerTestOneInput`) serves only as an entry point and is not the root cause. It supplies                      
                             arbitrary RTF content to the parser, triggering the deserialization logic.                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Code Areas to Investigate:                                                                                                                                                        
                                `RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject`  location where embedded-object streams are fed into `ObjectInputStream`.                                                             
                                `TextExtractor` and `RTFParser` modules  to trace how embedded data is located, extracted, and passed down to deserialization.                                                 
                                Any utility or helper methods around deserialization (e.g., custom `readObject` methods in Jazzers instrumentation or Tika classes).                                           
                                Configuration or extension points that govern which classes can be instantiated during deserialization.                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Reviewing these areas will provide a holistic understanding of how untrusted RTF content leads to unsafe deserialization and potential remote code execution.                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                                                                                                
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                                                                                                      
                             <issue>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             == Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution                                                                                  
                             Unrestricted class/object creation based on externally controlled data may allow                                                                                                    
                             remote code execution depending on available classes on the classpath.                                                                                                              
                                     at jaz.Zer.reportFinding(Zer.java:110)                                                                                                                                      
                                     at jaz.Zer.reportFindingIfEnabled(Zer.java:105)                                                                                                                             
                                     at jaz.Zer.readObject(Zer.java:377)                                                                                                                                         
                                     at java.base/jdk.internal.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke0(Native Method)                                                                                           
                                     at java.base/jdk.internal.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(NativeMethodAccessorImpl.java:77)                                                                         
                                     at java.base/jdk.internal.reflect.DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.java:43)

                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Issue Analysis and Root Cause:                                                                                                                                                   
                                - In `RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject()`, when `state == EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA`, the code unconditionally creates a plain `ObjectInputStream` over                       
                             attacker-controlled bytes (lines 215217) and calls `.readObject()`.                                                                                                                
                                - This allows arbitrary classes on the classpath to be instantiated and executed, leading to a high-severity remote code execution vulnerability.                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Preservation of Existing Functionality:                                                                                                                                          
                                - We must continue to capture the raw embedded bytes, record metadata, and invoke `extractObj(...)` so that downstream consumers still see something in place                  
                             of the Java object data.                                                                                                                                                            
                                - We must preserve the memory-limit checks, metadata setting for content length, and naming logic already in place.                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Strategy: Disable Unsafe Deserialization and Emit Raw Blob                                                                                                                       
                                - Replace the entire `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` branch in `handleCompletedObject()` with logic that:                                                                               
                                  a. Records in metadata that this is a Java object blob (e.g., via `RTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS` or an override content type).                                                        
                                  b. Does *not* call `new ObjectInputStream(...).readObject()`.                                                                                                                  
                                  c. Passes the original byte array directly to `extractObj(...)` as an opaque binary, e.g. with content type `application/octet-stream`.                                        
                                  d. Optionally, record a security-aware exception or warning in metadata via `EmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException(...)` to signal that deserialization was                     
                             intentionally skipped.                                                                                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Implementation Steps:                                                                                                                                                            
                                a. In `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`, locate the `else if (state == EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA)` block (around line 213).                                                                   
                                b. Replace lines 214225 with:                                                                                                                                                   
                                   ```java                                                                                                                                                                       
                                   } else if (state == EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA) {                                                                                                                                 
                                       // SECURITY FIX: disable unsafe Java deserialization.                                                                                                                     
                                       // Treat the serialized-object data as an opaque binary blob.                                                                                                             
                                       metadata.set(RTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS, "javaobjdata-raw");                                                                                                                   
                                       metadata.set(                                                                                                                                                             
                                           TikaCoreProperties.CONTENT_TYPE_PARSER_OVERRIDE,                                                                                                                      
                                           MediaType.application("octet-stream").toString());                                                                                                                    
                                       // Record that deserialization was skipped for security.                                                                                                                  
                                       EmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException(                                                                                                                                     
                                           new TikaException("Java-serialized-object deserialization is disabled"),                                                                                              
                                           metadata);                                                                                                                                                            
                                       // Pass the raw bytes through for embedding as binary                                                                                                                     
                                       extractObj(bytes, handler, metadata);                                                                                                                                     
                                   }                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                c. Import any missing classes (e.g. `MediaType.application`, `TikaException`, `EmbeddedDocumentUtil`).                                                                           
                                d. Leave all other branches and the final `reset()` call unchanged.                                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Justification:                                                                                                                                                                   
                                - By diverting the `JAVA_OBJDATA` branch to blob extraction, we eliminate any call to `ObjectInputStream.readObject()`, thereby removing the RCE vector.                         
                                - Consumers still receive the exact embedded data as a binary attachment, preserving something rather than silently dropping content.                                          
                                - Metadata flags make it clear downstream that this was originally Java-serialized data.                                                                                         
                                - Memory limits, naming conventions, and the overall embedded-document pipeline remain untouchedno harness or test code needs adjustment.                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. Side-Effect Mitigation:                                                                                                                                                          
                                - Any client code or existing tests that previously relied on seeing the `toString()` of a deserialized object will now see raw bytes.                                           
                                - To mitigate: update documentation or release notes indicating that RTF-embedded Java object support is disabled for security, and that consumers should parse                  
                             the raw blob themselves if needed.                                                                                                                                                  
                                - If future secure deserialization with class whitelisting is desired, it can be implemented in a follow-on patch (e.g., via a `TikaSecureObjectInputStream`                     
                             subclass or Java 9+ filters), but this quick fix fully eliminates the vulnerability with minimal code churn.                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             7. Implementation Impact:                                                                                                                                                           
                                - No changes to harness/fuzzing code; fuzz tests will now see this branch taken but will not trigger deserialization.                                                            
                                - No change to utility methods or external dependencies.                                                                                                                         
                                - Existing tests around generic embedded-document handling remain green, since the `extractObj(...)  parseEmbedded(...)` path is still invoked.                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             8. Verification:                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Add a unit test feeding an RTF snippet with `\javaobjdata` to verify that:                                                                                                     
                                   No deserialization occurs (e.g. by placing a custom `DataInputStream` payload).                                                                                              
                                   The resulting embedded document is reported as `application/octet-stream`.                                                                                                   
                                - Run full Tika test suite and confirm no regressions.                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===

                             -            }                                                                                                                                                                      
                             -        } else if (state == EMB_STATE.NADA) {                                                                                                                                      
                             -            //swallow...no start for pict or embed?!                                                                                                                               
                             +            // SECURITY FIX: disable unsafe Java deserialization.                                                                                                                  
                             +            // Treat the serialized-object data as an opaque binary blob.                                                                                                          
                             +            metadata.set(RTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS, "javaobjdata-raw");                                                                                                                
                             +            metadata.set(                                                                                                                                                          
                             +                    TikaCoreProperties.CONTENT_TYPE_PARSER_OVERRIDE,                                                                                                               
                             +                    MediaType.application("octet-stream").toString());                                                                                                             
                             +            // Record that deserialization was skipped for security.                                                                                                               
                             +            EmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException(                                                                                                                                  
                             +                    new TikaException("Java-serialized-object deserialization is disabled"),                                                                                       
                             +                    metadata);                                                                                                                                                     
                             +            // Pass the raw bytes through for embedding as binary.                                                                                                                 
                             +            extractObj(bytes, handler, metadata);                                                                                                                                  
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                      reset();                                                                                                                                                                   
                                  }

                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                             The fuzzer detected a high-severity remote code execution issue in the RTF parsers embeddedobject handler: unguarded Java deserialization of external data via                    
                             `ObjectInputStream.readObject()`. In response, a patch was attempted that disables unsafe deserialization for the `JAVA_OBJDATA` state, treats the data as opaque                   
                             binary, records a security exception in the metadata, and passes the raw bytes to the extractor. After applying the patch, the Microsoftmodule parser failed to                    
                             compile with a cascade of syntax errors (illegal start of type, invalid method declaration, unexpected tokens), indicating malformed Java codemost likely from                     
                             misaligned braces or misplaced statements in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`.                                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Initial Issue                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - A Jazzer fuzzing session reported a `FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution` during RTF parsing.                                                                       
                                - Stack trace highlights:                                                                                                                                                        
                                  * `RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject(...)` invoking `ObjectInputStream.readObject()`.                                                                                     
                                  * Unrestricted deserialization of attackercontrolled bytes can instantiate arbitrary classes on the classpath, leading to code execution.                                     
                                - The vulnerable code path is specifically the `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` branch in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`.                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Important Observations                                                                                                                                                           
                                - Deserialization is triggered by embedded Java object data within an RTF file.                                                                                                
                                - No classfiltering or sandboxing is applied before calling `readObject()`.                                                                                                     
                                - The vulnerability is marked high by the fuzzer and is reproducible.                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Patch Attempt                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Removed the original `try { new ObjectInputStream(...).readObject(); ... } catch (ClassNotFoundException)` block.                                                              
                                - Introduced a securityfocused block:                                                                                                                                           
                                  * Sets `RTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS` to a sentinel `"javaobjdata-raw"`.                                                                                                              
                                  * Overrides content type to `application/octet-stream`.                                                                                                                        
                                  * Calls `EmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException(new TikaException("Java-serialized-object deserialization is disabled"), metadata)`.                                             
                                  * Invokes `extractObj(bytes, handler, metadata)` to pass raw data onward.                                                                                                      
                                - Intended to disable unsafe deserialization and preserve the binary payload for downstream processing.                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Patch Result and Compilation Log                                                                                                                                                 
                                - The Microsoft parser module fails compilation with ~24 errors in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`.                                                                                      
                                - Representative errors:                                                                                                                                                         
                                  * illegal start of type                                                                                                                                                      
                                  * identifier expected                                                                                                                                                        
                                  * invalid method declaration; return type required                                                                                                                           
                                  * Multiple class, interface, enum, or record expected                                                                                                                        
                                - Errors point to lines ~227280, suggesting a large malformed regionlikely due to missing or extra braces, misplaced parentheses, or stray tokens introduced                   
                             by the patch.                                                                                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Areas for Further Investigation                                                                                                                                                  
                                - The `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` branch in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`: verify correct opening/closing of braces and that all statements are inside the method body.                   
                                - Correct usage and import of `EmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException(...)`: ensure the method signature matches and imports are in place.                                         
                                - Surrounding code structure (other `else if` blocks): confirm no accidental edit of adjacent conditional logic.                                                                 
                                - Build configurations for the Microsoft parser module: validate Java language level and dependencies for `application("octet-stream")` and related APIs.                        
                                - Test coverage for other embedding states (`EMB_STATE.OLE`, `EMB_STATE.PICT`, etc.) to understand how similar patterns are handled and to avoid introducing new                 
                             syntax issues elsewhere.

                             188:    protected void handleCompletedObject() throws IOException, SAXException, TikaException {                                                                                    
                             189:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             190:        byte[] bytes = os.toByteArray();                                                                                                                                        
                             191:        if (state == EMB_STATE.OBJDATA) {                                                                                                                                       
                             192:            RTFObjDataParser objParser = new RTFObjDataParser(memoryLimitInKb);                                                                                                 
                             193:            try {                                                                                                                                                               
                             194:                byte[] objBytes = objParser.parse(bytes, metadata, unknownFilenameCount);                                                                                       
                             195:                extractObj(objBytes, handler, metadata);                                                                                                                        
                             196:            } catch (IOException e) {                                                                                                                                           
                             197:                EmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException(e, metadata);                                                                                                              
                             198:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             199:        } else if (state == EMB_STATE.PICT) {                                                                                                                                   
                             200:            String filePath = metadata.get(RTFMetadata.RTF_PICT_META_PREFIX + "wzDescription");                                                                                 
                             201:            if (filePath != null && filePath.length() > 0) {                                                                                                                    
                             202:                metadata.set(TikaCoreProperties.EMBEDDED_RELATIONSHIP_ID, filePath);                                                                                            
                             203:                metadata.set(TikaCoreProperties.RESOURCE_NAME_KEY, FilenameUtils.getName(filePath));                                                                            
                             204:                metadata.set(TikaCoreProperties.ORIGINAL_RESOURCE_NAME, filePath);                                                                                              
                             205:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             206:            metadata.set(RTFMetadata.THUMBNAIL, Boolean.toString(inObject));                                                                                                    
                             207:            if (isPictBitmap) {                                                                                                                                                 
                             208:                metadata.set(                                                                                                                                                   
                             209:                        TikaCoreProperties.CONTENT_TYPE_PARSER_OVERRIDE, "image/x-rtf-raw-bitmap");                                                                             
                             210:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             211:            extractObj(bytes, handler, metadata);                                                                                                                               
                             212:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             ```
