                             17:package org.apache.tika.extractor;                                                                                                                                               
                             18:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             19:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             20:import java.io.IOException;                                                                                                                                                      
                             21:import java.io.Serializable;                                                                                                                                                     
                             22:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             23:import org.xml.sax.ContentHandler;                                                                                                                                               
                             24:import org.xml.sax.SAXException;                                                                                                                                                 
                             25:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             26:import org.apache.tika.config.TikaConfig;                                                                                                                                        
                             27:import org.apache.tika.detect.Detector;                                                                                                                                          
                             28:import org.apache.tika.io.TikaInputStream;                                                                                                                                       
                             29:import org.apache.tika.metadata.Metadata;                                                                                                                                        
                             30:import org.apache.tika.metadata.TikaCoreProperties;                                                                                                                              
                             31:import org.apache.tika.mime.MediaType;                                                                                                                                           
                             32:import org.apache.tika.mime.MimeType;                                                                                                                                            
                             33:import org.apache.tika.mime.MimeTypeException;                                                                                                                                   
                             34:import org.apache.tika.mime.MimeTypes;                                                                                                                                           
                             35:import org.apache.tika.parser.AutoDetectParser;                                                                                                                                  
                             36:import org.apache.tika.parser.CompositeParser;                                                                                                                                   
                             37:import org.apache.tika.parser.ParseContext;                                                                                                                                      
                             38:import org.apache.tika.parser.Parser;                                                                                                                                            
                             39:import org.apache.tika.parser.ParserDecorator;                                                                                                                                   
                             40:import org.apache.tika.parser.PasswordProvider;                                                                                                                                  
                             41:import org.apache.tika.parser.StatefulParser;                                                                                                                                    
                             42:import org.apache.tika.utils.ExceptionUtils;                                                                                                                                     
                             43:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             44:/**                                                                                                                                                                              
                             45: * Utility class to handle common issues with embedded documents.                                                                                                                
                             46: * <p/>                                                                                                                                                                          
                             47: * Use statically if all that is needed is getting the EmbeddedDocumentExtractor.                                                                                                
                             48: * Otherwise, instantiate an instance.                                                                                                                                           
                             49: * <p/>                                                                                                                                                                          
                             50: * Note: This is not thread safe.  Make sure to instantiate one per thread.                                                                                                      
                             51: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             52:public class EmbeddedDocumentUtil implements Serializable {                                                                                                                      
                             53:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             54:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             55:    private final ParseContext context;                                                                                                                                          
                             56:    private final EmbeddedDocumentExtractor embeddedDocumentExtractor;                                                                                                           
                             57:    //these are lazily initialized and can be null                                                                                                                               
                             58:    private TikaConfig tikaConfig;                                                                                                                                               
                             59:    private MimeTypes mimeTypes;                                                                                                                                                 
                             60:    private Detector detector;                                                                                                                                                   
                             61:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             62:    public EmbeddedDocumentUtil(ParseContext context) {                                                                                                                          
                             63:        this.context = context;                                                                                                                                                  
                             64:        this.embeddedDocumentExtractor = getEmbeddedDocumentExtractor(context);                                                                                                  
                             65:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             66:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             67:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             68:     * This offers a uniform way to get an EmbeddedDocumentExtractor from a ParseContext.                                                                                        
                             69:     * As of Tika 1.15, an AutoDetectParser will automatically be added to parse                                                                                                 
                             70:     * embedded documents if no Parser.class is specified in the ParseContext.                                                                                                   
                             71:     * <p/>                                                                                                                                                                      
                             72:     * If you'd prefer not to parse embedded documents, set Parser.class                                                                                                         
                             73:     * to {@link org.apache.tika.parser.EmptyParser} in the ParseContext.                                                                                                        
                             74:     *                                                                                                                                                                           
                             75:     * @param context                                                                                                                                                            
                             76:     * @return EmbeddedDocumentExtractor                                                                                                                                         
                             77:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             78:    public static EmbeddedDocumentExtractor getEmbeddedDocumentExtractor(ParseContext context) {                                                                                 
                             79:        EmbeddedDocumentExtractor extractor = context.get(EmbeddedDocumentExtractor.class);                                                                                      
                             80:        if (extractor != null) {                                                                                                                                                 
                             81:            return extractor;                                                                                                                                                    
                             82:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             83:        //ensure that an AutoDetectParser is                                                                                                                                     
                             84:        //available for parsing embedded docs TIKA-2096                                                                                                                          
                             85:        Parser embeddedParser = context.get(Parser.class);                                                                                                                       
                             86:        if (embeddedParser == null) {                                                                                                                                            
                             87:            TikaConfig tikaConfig = context.get(TikaConfig.class);                                                                                                               
                             88:            if (tikaConfig == null) {                                                                                                                                            
                             89:                context.set(Parser.class, new AutoDetectParser());                                                                                                               
                             90:            } else {                                                                                                                                                             
                             91:                context.set(Parser.class, new AutoDetectParser(tikaConfig));                                                                                                     
                             92:            }                                                                                                                                                                    
                             93:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             94:        EmbeddedDocumentExtractor ex = new ParsingEmbeddedDocumentExtractor(context);                                                                                            
                             95:        context.set(EmbeddedDocumentExtractor.class, ex);                                                                                                                        
                             96:        return ex;                                                                                                                                                               
                             97:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             98:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             99:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             100:     * Utility function to get the Parser that was sent in to the                                                                                                               
                             101:     * ParseContext to handle embedded documents.  If it is stateful,                                                                                                           
                             102:     * unwrap it to get its stateless delegating parser.                                                                                                                        
                             103:     * <p>                                                                                                                                                                      
                             104:     * If there is no Parser in the parser context, this will return null.                                                                                                      
                             105:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             106:     * @param context                                                                                                                                                           
                             107:     * @return                                                                                                                                                                  
                             108:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             109:    public static Parser getStatelessParser(ParseContext context) {                                                                                                             
                             110:        Parser p = context.get(Parser.class);                                                                                                                                   
                             111:        if (p == null) {                                                                                                                                                        
                             112:            return null;                                                                                                                                                        
                             113:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             114:        if (p instanceof StatefulParser) {                                                                                                                                      
                             115:            return ((StatefulParser) p).getWrappedParser();                                                                                                                     
                             116:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             117:        return p;                                                                                                                                                               
                             118:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             119:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             120:    public PasswordProvider getPasswordProvider() {                                                                                                                             
                             121:        return context.get(PasswordProvider.class);                                                                                                                             
                             122:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             123:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             124:    public Detector getDetector() {                                                                                                                                             
                             125:        //be as lazy as possible and cache                                                                                                                                      
                             126:        Detector localDetector = context.get(Detector.class);                                                                                                                   
                             127:        if (localDetector != null) {                                                                                                                                            
                             128:            return localDetector;                                                                                                                                               
                             129:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             130:        if (detector != null) {                                                                                                                                                 
                             131:            return detector;                                                                                                                                                    
                             132:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             133:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             134:        detector = getTikaConfig().getDetector();                                                                                                                               
                             135:        return detector;                                                                                                                                                        
                             136:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             137:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             138:    public MimeTypes getMimeTypes() {                                                                                                                                           
                             139:        MimeTypes localMimeTypes = context.get(MimeTypes.class);                                                                                                                
                             140:        //be as lazy as possible and cache the mimeTypes                                                                                                                        
                             141:        if (localMimeTypes != null) {                                                                                                                                           
                             142:            return localMimeTypes;                                                                                                                                              
                             143:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             144:        if (mimeTypes != null) {                                                                                                                                                
                             145:            return mimeTypes;                                                                                                                                                   
                             146:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             147:        mimeTypes = getTikaConfig().getMimeRepository();                                                                                                                        
                             148:        return mimeTypes;                                                                                                                                                       
                             149:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             150:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             151:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             152:     * @return Returns a {@link TikaConfig} -- trying to find it first in the ParseContext                                                                                      
                             153:     * that was included during initialization, and then creating a new one from                                                                                                
                             154:     * via {@link TikaConfig#getDefaultConfig()} if it can't find one in the                                                                                                    
                             155:     * ParseContext. This caches the default config so that it only has to be created once.                                                                                     
                             156:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             157:    public TikaConfig getTikaConfig() {                                                                                                                                         
                             158:        //be as lazy as possible and cache the TikaConfig                                                                                                                       
                             159:        if (tikaConfig == null) {                                                                                                                                               
                             160:            tikaConfig = context.get(TikaConfig.class);                                                                                                                         
                             161:            if (tikaConfig == null) {                                                                                                                                           
                             162:                tikaConfig = TikaConfig.getDefaultConfig();                                                                                                                     
                             163:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             164:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             165:        return tikaConfig;                                                                                                                                                      
                             166:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             167:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             168:    public String getExtension(TikaInputStream is, Metadata metadata) {                                                                                                         
                             169:        String mimeString = metadata.get(Metadata.CONTENT_TYPE);                                                                                                                
                             170:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             171:        //use the buffered mimetypes as default                                                                                                                                 
                             172:        MimeTypes localMimeTypes = getMimeTypes();                                                                                                                              
                             173:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             174:        MimeType mimeType = null;                                                                                                                                               
                             175:        boolean detected = false;                                                                                                                                               
                             176:        if (mimeString != null) {                                                                                                                                               
                             177:            try {                                                                                                                                                               
                             178:                mimeType = localMimeTypes.forName(mimeString);                                                                                                                  
                             179:            } catch (MimeTypeException e) {                                                                                                                                     
                             180:                //swallow                                                                                                                                                       
                             181:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             182:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             183:        if (mimeType == null) {                                                                                                                                                 
                             184:            try {                                                                                                                                                               
                             185:                MediaType mediaType = getDetector().detect(is, metadata);                                                                                                       
                             186:                mimeType = localMimeTypes.forName(mediaType.toString());                                                                                                        
                             187:                detected = true;                                                                                                                                                
                             188:                is.reset();                                                                                                                                                     
                             189:            } catch (IOException | MimeTypeException e) {                                                                                                                       
                             190:                //swallow                                                                                                                                                       
                             191:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             192:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             193:        if (mimeType != null) {                                                                                                                                                 
                             194:            if (detected) {                                                                                                                                                     
                             195:                //set or correct the mime type                                                                                                                                  
                             196:                metadata.set(Metadata.CONTENT_TYPE, mimeType.toString());                                                                                                       
                             197:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             198:            return mimeType.getExtension();                                                                                                                                     
                             199:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             200:        return ".bin";                                                                                                                                                          
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>

                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Identify and correct the misplaced braces in RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject:                                                                                             
                                - The last patch inserted an extra closing brace (`}`) before the `else if (state == EMB_STATE.NADA)` line, causing the Java compiler to see method or                          
                             classlevel code where it expected only type declarations.                                                                                                                          
                                - We must remove the superfluous `}` and ensure exactly one brace closes the `JAVA_OBJDATA` branch before the next `else if`.                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Rewrite the `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` branch in full, replacing the unsafe deserialization block (lines ~213224) with a clean stub that mirrors the existing                     
                             `OBJDATA` and `PICT` patterns:                                                                                                                                                      
                                a. Locate:                                                                                                                                                                       
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   } else if (state == EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA) {                                                                                                                                 
                                       // old trycatch code...                                                                                                                                                  
                                   } else if (state == EMB_STATE.NADA) {                                                                                                                                         
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                b. Remove all lines from the `{` after `JAVA_OBJDATA` through the matching closing brace of that branch (including any stray `}` you previously added).                          
                                c. Insert the following block:                                                                                                                                                   
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   } else if (state == EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA) {                                                                                                                                 
                                       // SECURITY FIX: disable unsafe Java deserialization.                                                                                                                     
                                       // Treat the serialized object data as opaque binary.                                                                                                                     
                                       metadata.set(RTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS, "javaobjdata-raw");                                                                                                                   
                                       metadata.set(                                                                                                                                                             
                                           TikaCoreProperties.CONTENT_TYPE_PARSER_OVERRIDE,                                                                                                                      
                                           MediaType.application("octet-stream").toString());                                                                                                                    
                                       // Record that deserialization was skipped for security.                                                                                                                  
                                       EmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException(                                                                                                                                     
                                           new TikaException("Java-serialized-object deserialization is disabled"),                                                                                              
                                           metadata);                                                                                                                                                            
                                       // Pass the raw bytes to the embeddedobject extractor.                                                                                                                   
                                       extractObj(bytes, handler, metadata);                                                                                                                                     
                                   } else if (state == EMB_STATE.NADA) {                                                                                                                                         
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                - Note: There is now exactly one `}` closing the `JAVA_OBJDATA` block, and the `else if (state == EMB_STATE.NADA)` follows immediately.                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Verify imports in RTFEmbObjHandler.java:                                                                                                                                         
                                - Ensure the following imports are present (they likely are, but doublecheck):                                                                                                  
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                  import org.apache.tika.exception.TikaException;                                                                                                                                
                                  import org.apache.tika.extractor.EmbeddedDocumentUtil;                                                                                                                         
                                  import org.apache.tika.metadata.RTFMetadata;                                                                                                                                   
                                  import org.apache.tika.metadata.TikaCoreProperties;                                                                                                                            
                                  import org.apache.tika.mime.MediaType;                                                                                                                                         
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - No new external dependencies are needed.                                                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Preserve existing functionality:                                                                                                                                                 
                                - Downstream consumers still receive the raw byte array via `extractObj(...)`.                                                                                                   
                                - Metadata flags (`EMB_CLASS` set to `"javaobjdata-raw"` and content type `application/octet-stream`) clearly signal that deserialization was skipped.                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Compile and run the full Microsoftmodule suite:                                                                                                                                 
                                - Confirm that the brace mismatch and syntax errors are resolved.                                                                                                                
                                - Ensure no regressions in other `handleCompletedObject` branches (`OBJDATA`, `PICT`, `NADA`) by running unit and integration tests.                                             
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Justification:                                                                                                                                                                      
                             - This minimal change removes unsafe Java deserialization, replacing it with the same errorrecording and extraction pattern used elsewhere in `RTFEmbObjHandler`.                  
                             - By fixing brace alignment, the compilation errors (illegal starts, misplaced method declarations) will disappear.                                                                 
                             - Existing logic paths for other `EMB_STATE` values remain untouched, preserving functionality.                                                                                     
                             - No changes to harness or external libraries are made, complying with the security fix requirements.                                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>

                             == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                                                                                                                      
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             The initial issue was flagged by the Jazzer fuzzer as a highseverity security finding: in the RTF parsers embeddedobject handler, untrusted data under the                       
                             `JAVA_OBJDATA` state was being deserialized via `new ObjectInputStream(...).readObject()`, opening a remote code execution vector if malicious classes were present                 
                             on the classpath.                                                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             The provided patch replaces the risky deserialization block with a disable deserialization stub: it annotates the data as raw binary, records a security                          
                             exception in the document metadata, and forwards the unparsed bytes for embedding.                                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             After applying the patch, the Maven builds test phase failed during the Surefire plugin execution, reporting that it could not resolve the artifact descriptor for                 
                             `org.apache.maven.shared:maven-common-artifact-filters:jar:3.1.1`. No tests ran to completion due to this dependency resolution error.                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Initial Issue                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - A Jazzerdriven fuzzer input triggered                                                                                                                                         
                                  com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution                                                                                                
                                  within `RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject`.                                                                                                                               
                                - Stack trace shows control flow through                                                                                                                                         
                                  `Zer.readObject`  `ObjectInputStream.readObject`  `RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject`.                                                                                  
                                - In the `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` branch, arbitrary serialized Java objects from the RTF stream are deserialized without restriction, recorded in metadata, and                  
                             then converted to text and reparsed.                                                                                                                                               
                                - This constitutes unsafe, externally controlled deserialization and is a confirmed highseverity security risk.                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Patch Attempt                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Location: `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`, inside the `if (state == EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA)` block.                                                                                    
                                - Original code removed:                                                                                                                                                         
                                   Construction of `ObjectInputStream` over the raw bytes                                                                                                                       
                                   `readObject()` invocation and class name capture                                                                                                                             
                                   Conversion of the objects `toString()` output back to bytes for text extraction                                                                                             
                                - New code inserted:                                                                                                                                                             
                                   Sets `RTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS` to `"javaobjdata-raw"`                                                                                                                          
                                   Forces content type override to `application/octet-stream`                                                                                                                   
                                   Calls `EmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException(new TikaException("Java-serialized-object deserialization is disabled"), metadata)`                                              
                                   Passes the raw `bytes` directly to `extractObj(...)`                                                                                                                         
                                - Comments label this as a SECURITY FIX to disable unsafe deserialization.                                                                                                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Patch Result                                                                                                                                                                     
                                - Build command (`mvn test`) reached the Surefire plugin phase in the `fuzz-targets` project.                                                                                    
                                - Error: Failed to read artifact descriptor for                                                                                                                                  
                                  `org.apache.maven.shared:maven-common-artifact-filters:jar:3.1.1`                                                                                                              
                                - The test suite did not run; the build stopped due to unresolved plugin dependency.                                                                                             
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Areas for Further Investigation                                                                                                                                                  
                                - Maven configuration in the `fuzz-targets` module / parent POM, especially dependency declarations for `maven-common-artifact-filters` and pluginRepositories.                  
                                - The `RTFEmbObjHandler` class and its interactions with `EmbeddedDocumentUtil` to ensure consistent error reporting.                                                            
                                - Other deserialization code paths in the RTF parser (e.g., how nonJava embed states are handled).                                                                              
                                - The broader build setup for Tikas fuzz targets and how new utility calls (e.g., `EmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException`) may introduce missing dependencies.

                             91:          </plugin>                                                                                                                                                              
                             92:          <plugin>                                                                                                                                                               
                             93:            <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>                                                                                                                          
                             94:            <artifactId>maven-antrun-plugin</artifactId>                                                                                                                         
                             95:            <version>${maven.antrun.version}</version>                                                                                                                           
                             96:            <executions>                                                                                                                                                         
                             97:              <execution>                                                                                                                                                        
                             98:                <goals>                                                                                                                                                          
                             99:                  <goal>run</goal>                                                                                                                                               
                             100:                </goals>                                                                                                                                                        
                             101:                <phase>deploy</phase>                                                                                                                                           
                             102:                <configuration>                                                                                                                                                 
                             103:                  <target>                                                                                                                                                      
                             104:                    <mkdir dir="${basedir}/target/${project.version}" />                                                                                                        
                             105:                    <copy todir="${basedir}/target/${project.version}" flatten="true">                                                                                          
                             106:                      <fileset dir="${basedir}">                                                                                                                                
                             107:                        <include name="CHANGES.txt" />                                                                                                                          
                             108:                        <include name="target/*-src.zip*" />                                                                                                                    
                             109:                        <include                                                                                                                                                
                             name="tika-parsers/tika-parsers-extended/tika-parser-scientific-package/target/tika-parser-scientific-package-${project.version}.jar*" />                                           
                             110:                        <include                                                                                                                                                
                             name="tika-parsers/tika-parsers-extended/tika-parser-sqlite3-package/target/tika-parser-sqlite3-package-${project.version}.jar*" />                                                 
                             111:                        <include name="tika-parsers/tika-parsers-ml/tika-parser-nlp-package/target/tika-parser-nlp-package-${project.version}.jar*" />                          
                             112:                        <include name="tika-app/target/tika-app-${project.version}.jar*" />                                                                                     
                             113:                        <include name="tika-server/tika-server-standard/target/tika-server-standard-${project.version}.jar*" />                                                 
                             114:                        <include name="tika-server/tika-server-standard/target/tika-server-standard-${project.version}-bin.tgz*" />                                             
                             115:                        <include name="tika-server/tika-server-standard/target/tika-server-standard-${project.version}-bin.zip*" />                                             
                             116:                        <include name="tika-eval/tika-eval-app/target/tika-eval-app-${project.version}.jar*" />                                                                 
                             117:                      </fileset>                                                                                                                                                
                             118:                    </copy>                                                                                                                                                     
                             119:                    <checksum algorithm="SHA-512" fileext=".sha512">                                                                                                            
                             120:                      <fileset dir="${basedir}/target/${project.version}">                                                                                                      
                             121:                        <include name="*.tgz" />                                                                                                                                
                             122:                        <include name="*.zip" />                                                                                                                                
                             123:                        <include name="*.?ar" />                                                                                                                                
                             124:                      </fileset>                                                                                                                                                
                             125:                    </checksum>                                                                                                                                                 
                             126:                    <checksum file="${basedir}/target/${project.version}/tika-${project.version}-src.zip" algorithm="SHA-512" property="checksum" />                            
                             127:<!-- this spacing is less than ideal, but if you indent here, the vote.txt file will have the leading spaces -->                                                                
                             128:                    <echo file="${basedir}/target/vote.txt">                                                                                                                    
                             129:From: ${username}@apache.org                                                                                                                                                    
                             130:To: dev@tika.apache.org                                                                                                                                                         
                             131:user@tika.apache.org

                             135:https://dist.apache.org/repos/dist/dev/tika/${project.version}                                                                                                                  
                             136:

                             138:https://github.com/apache/tika/tree/{project.version}-rcN/                                                                                                                      
                             139:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             140:The SHA-512 checksum of the archive is                                                                                                                                          
                             141:${checksum}.                                                                                                                                                                    
                             142:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             143:In addition, a staged maven repository is available here:                                                                                                                       
                             144:https://repository.apache.org/content/repositories/orgapachetika-.../org/apache/tika                                                                                            
                             145:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             146:Please vote on releasing this package as Apache Tika ${project.version}.                                                                                                        
                             147:The vote is open for the next 72 hours and passes if a majority of at                                                                                                           
                             148:least three +1 Tika PMC votes are cast.                                                                                                                                         
                             149:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             150:[ ] +1 Release this package as Apache Tika ${project.version}                                                                                                                   
                             151:[ ] -1 Do not release this package because...${line.separator}                                                                                                                  
                             152:                    </echo>                                                                                                                                                     
                             153:                    <echo />                                                                                                                                                    
                             154:                    <echo>                                                                                                                                                      
                             155:                      The release candidate has been prepared in:                                                                                                               
                             156:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             157:                      ${basedir}/target/${project.version}                                                                                                                      
                             158:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             159:                      Please deploy it to people.apache.org like this:                                                                                                          
                             160:

                             162:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             163:                      A release vote template has been generated for you:                                                                                                       
                             164:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             165:                      file://${basedir}/target/vote.txt                                                                                                                         
                             166:                    </echo>                                                                                                                                                     
                             167:                    <echo />                                                                                                                                                    
                             168:                  </target>                                                                                                                                                     
                             169:                </configuration>                                                                                                                                                
                             170:              </execution>                                                                                                                                                      
                             171:            </executions>                                                                                                                                                       
                             172:            <dependencies>
